<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-82-0323 </DOCNO><TEXT>The thickness of thin natural oxide films formed on silicon, nickel, aluminium,iron, tantalum and zirconium has been measured using nuclear reactionanalysis (NRA) and Auger electron spectroscopy (AES) in combination withion beam sputtering. It is shown that ion beam effects severely limitthe use of AES and ion beam sputtering in measuring thin oxide thicknesses.Relatively non-destructive techniques such as NRA or angle-resolved x-rayphotoelectron spectroscopy (XPS) provide more reliable information.</TEXT></DOC>